title: Inter-Party Relationships
new-page: true
view-if: erc_inter_party_relationships_timer <= 0
tags: erc_party
is-card: true
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; erc_inter_party_relationships_timer = 6;
card-image: img/parties/frontpopular.jpg
face-image: img/parties/frontpopular.jpg

# TODO: Proper weighting of relations for different comuns leaders (just as we did with PSC). Should we do the same with CUP factions in power?

= Inter-Party Relationships

ERC cannot govern by itself yet. Because we do not have an electoral majority, we need the support of other parties. Up until 2010, we were part of a tripartite coalition with PSC and ICV-EUiA [? if csqp_formed: (now part of CSQP)?][? if cecp_formed: (now part of CECP)?][? if ecp_formed: (now part of ECP)?], but its failures have left us with strained relations, specially with the PSC. The new surge of support for independence also opens new avenues of cooperation through shared national lines, namely with [? if not unio_split: CiU?][? if pdcat_formed and not pdcat_split: pdcat?][? if cdc_formed: CDC?][? if dl_formed: DL?][?if not erc_in_jxcat and jxcat_formed: JxCat?][? if erc_in_jxcat and jxcat_formed: CDC?][? if junts_formed: Junts ?][? if si_parlament_s> 0: , SI?] and CUP.

- @jxsi_relations: We need to work on national unity within JxSi!
- @jxcat_relations: We need to work on national unity within JxCat!
- @ciu_relations: We need to work on national unity with CiU ([+ciu_ideology+])
- @pdcat_nosplit_relations: We need to work on national unity with PdCat ([+pdcat_ideology+])
- @cdc_relations: We need to work on national unity with CDC ([+cdc_ideology+])
- @dl_relations: We need to work on national unity with DL ([+dl_ideology+])
- @jxcat_noerc_relations: We need to work on national unity with JxCat ([+jxcat_ideology+])
- @junts_relations: We need to work on national unity with Junts ([+junts_ideology+])
- @cup_relations: Left and national unity at the same time? Let's work on it with CUP ([+cup_ideology+])
- @si_relations: Left and national unity, plus people willing to work with us? Let's talk with SI ([+si_ideology+])
- @icv_relations: We could use boosted trust with ICV-EUiA ([+icv_ideology+])
- @csqp_relations: Let's build bridges with the new left, CSQP ([+csqp_ideology+])
- @cecp_relations: Let's build bridges with the new left, CECP ([+cecp_ideology+])
- @ecp_relations: We should build bridges with the left, ECP ([+ecp_ideology+])
- @psc_relations: Can we repair our relationship with the PSC ([+psc_ideology+])?
- @pdcat_split_relations: Should we lean closer to the more moderate PdCat ([+pdcat_ideology+])?
- @unio_relations: Can we convince the more Catalan wing of UDC ([+unio_ideology+]) to work with us?
- @pxc_relations: Maybe national unity should include the fringe Catalan far-right, PxC ([+pxc_ideology+])?
- @fnc_relations: Maybe national unity should include the fringe Catalan far-right, FNC ([+fnc_ideology+])?
- @erc_alone: ERC can stand alone for now.
- @easy_discard

@si_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: si_parlament_s > 0
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    Q.si_relations += 10*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
!}

SI are already quite aligned with us, and already eager to work together. Let's hope they retain popular support so we can build a strong alliance here. With the pro-independence movement on the rise, it's not like they are going to just disappear from the Parlament, right?

@jxsi_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: jxsi_formed and erc_in_jxsi
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    for (var party in Q.jxsi_parties) {
        if (party === "erc") continue;
        Q[party + "_relations"] += 8*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    }
    if (!Q.jxsi_parties.includes("cup")) {
        Q.cup_relations += 1;
    }
    if (Q.csqp_formed) {
        Q.csqp_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.cecp_formed) {
        Q.cecp_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.ecp_formed) {
        Q.ecp_relations -= 4;
    } else {
        Q.icv_relations -= 2;
    }
!}

The JxSí coalition is a naturally unstable one, but in the name of National Unity we are doing our best to keep it together.

@jxcat_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: jxcat_formed and erc_in_jxcat
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    for (var party in Q.jxcat_parties) {
        if (party === "erc") continue;
        Q[party + "_relations"] += 8*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    }
    if (!Q.jxcat_parties.includes("cup")) {
        Q.cup_relations += 1;
    }
    if (Q.csqp_formed) {
        Q.csqp_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.cecp_formed) {
        Q.cecp_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.ecp_formed) {
        Q.ecp_relations -= 5;
    } else {
        Q.icv_relations -= 2;
    }
!}

Just as with JxSí, the JxCat coalition is not the epitome of stability. But now that we are re-editing the National Unity formula, we are somewhat more used to it, and we are doing our best to keep it together.


@ciu_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1 
view-if: not unio_split
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    if (Q.erc_supporting && Q.cat_coalition.includes("ciu")) {
        Q.ciu_relations += 7*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
        Q.cup_realations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.erc_in_gob && Q.cat_coalition.includes("ciu")) {
        Q.ciu_relations += 4*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
        Q.cup_relations -= 1;
        Q.cat_coalition_dissent = -5;
    } else {
        Q.ciu_relations += 6*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
        Q.cup_relations -= 3;
    }
    if (Q.csqp_formed) {
        Q.csqp_relations -= 3;
    } else if (Q.cecp_formed) {
        Q.cecp_relations -= 3;
    } else if (Q.ecp_formed) {
        Q.ecp_relations -= 3;
    } else {
        Q.icv_relations -= 3;
    }
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_ciu = Q.cat_coalition.includes("ciu");
!}

[? if erc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_ciu: We are currently supporting a CiU government, which they already appreciate. Maybe this can bring us closer together? ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_ciu: We are currently governing together with CiU, which already creates some tensions. These move will hopefully smooth some of that over. ?][? if (not erc_supporting or not cat_coalition_includes_ciu) or (not erc_in_gob or not cat_coalition_includes_ciu): Without official institutional obligations to eachother for the moment, building ties with CiU is always easier. ?]The left parties are not particularly happy about these moves though.

