@cup_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: not cup_in_jxsi and not cup_in_jxcat
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    if (Q.cup_supporting && Q.cat_coalition.includes("erc")) {
        Q.cup_relations += 5*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    } else if (Q.erc_in_gob && Q.cat_coalition.includes("cup")) {
        Q.cup_relations += 7*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
        Q.cat_coalition_dissent = -5;
    } else {
        Q.cup_relations += 6*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    }
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_erc = Q.cat_coalition.includes("erc");
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_cup = Q.cat_coalition.includes("cup");
!}

[? if cup_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: CUP is currently supporting our government, which is already a balancing act. Hopefully this can bring us closer together. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_cup: We are currently governing together with CUP, which alread demonstrates our commitment to leftist values. Let's hope this formula can hold up for some time. ?][? if (not cup_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc) or (not erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_cup): Without official institutional obligations to eachother for the moment, building ties with CUP is always easier. ?]

@icv_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: not csqp_formed and not ceccp_formed and not ecp_formed
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    if (Q.icv_supporting && Q.cat_coalition.includes("erc")) {
        Q.icv_relations += 5*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    } else if (Q.erc_in_gob && Q.cat_coalition.includes("icv") || Q.cat_coalition.includes("icv") && Q.erc_supporting || Q.icv_supporting && Q.erc_supporting) {
        Q.icv_relations += 4*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
        Q.cat_coalition_dissent = -5;
    } else {
        Q.icv_relations += 6*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    }
    if (Q.junts_formed) {
        Q.junts_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.jxcat_formed && !Q.erc_in_jxcat) {
        Q.jxcat_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.dl_formed) {
        Q.dl_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.cdc_formed) {
        Q.cdc_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.pdcat_formed) {
        Q.pdcat_relations -= 2;
    } else {
        Q.ciu_relations -= 2;
    }
    if (Q.unio_split) {
        Q.unio_relations -= 2;
    }
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_icv = Q.cat_coalition.includes("icv");
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_erc = Q.cat_coalition.includes("erc");
!}

ICV-EUiA has been a longstanding ally of ERC, we a lot of shared goals on Republicanism and Social Justice. [? if icv_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: They are currently supporting our government, which does bring some friction. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_icv: Governing together does bring some friction though. ?][? if cat_coalition_includes_icv and erc_supporting: We are already supporting a government they are a part of. Not being part of it is bringing some friction though. ?][? if icv_supporting and erc_supporting: We are currently supporting the same government, which feels a bit underwhelming. We should be there as welll! ?]Nonetheless, hope to be able to build on those shared goals. By doing this, we may be somewhat alienating our more Catalanist allies to our right.

