ECP feels less like a natural ally of ERC than its predecessors. We still have a lot of shared goals on Republicanism and Social Justice, but the moderation in their demands is a bit disappointing. [? if ecp_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: They are currently supporting our government, which does bring some friction. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_ecp: Governing together does bring some friction though. ?][? if cat_coalition_includes_ecp and erc_supporting: We are already supporting a government they are a part of. Not being part of it is bringing some friction though. ?][? if ecp_supporting and erc_supporting: We are currently supporting the same government, which feels a bit underwhelming. We should be there as welll! ?]Nonetheless, hope to be able to build on those shared goals. By doing this, we may be somewhat alienating our more Catalanist allies to our right.

@psc_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: not psc_dissolved
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    if (Q.junts_formed) {
        Q.junts_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.jxcat_formed && !Q.erc_in_jxcat) {
        Q.jxcat_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.dl_formed) {
        Q.dl_relations -= 2; 
    } else if (Q.cdc_formed) {
        Q.cdc_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.pdcat_formed) {
        Q.pdcat_relations -= 2;
    } else {
        Q.ciu_relations -= 2;
    }
    if (Q.unio_split) {
        Q.unio_relations -= 2;
    }
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_psc = Q.cat_coalition.includes("psc");
    Q.cat_coalition_includes_erc = Q.cat_coalition.includes("erc");
!}
go-to: psc_relations_iceta if psc_leader = "Miquel Iceta"; psc_relations_parlon if psc_leader = "Nuria Parlon"; psc_relations_navarro if psc_leader = "Pere Navarro"; psc_relations_ros if psc_leader = "Àngel Ros"; psc_relations_tura if psc_leader = "Monsterrat Tura"

@psc_relations_iceta
on-arrival: {!
    var psc_factor = 2;
    if (Q.psc_supporting && Q.cat_coalition.includes("erc")) {
        Q.psc_relations += psc_factor*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    } else if (Q.erc_in_gob && Q.cat_coalition.includes("psc")) {
        Q.psc_relations += psc_factor*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
        Q.cat_coalition_dissent = -5;
    } else if (Q.erc_supporting && Q.cat_coalition.includes("psc")) {
        Q.psc_relations += psc_factor*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100) - 1;
    } else {
        Q.psc_relations += psc_factor*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    }
!}

Miquel Iceta's PSC is not particularly prone to collaborating with us, does not enjoy a lot of popularity, and is not particularly motivated to even reform the Spanish state. There is definitely some shared grounds, but its certainly not the most promising relationship to exist. [? if psc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: They are, at least, currently supporting our government. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_psc: Governing together does bring some friction on top of that. ?][? if erc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_psc: We are already supporting a government they are a part of. Not being part of it is bringing some friction though. ?]By doing this, we may be somewhat alienating our more Catalanist allies to our right.

