Pere Navarro's PSC is unstable and unpopular. His hard bet on a federal Spain and on self-determination rights without many supports for such move within the PSOE don't make it the most appealing option to voters or political allies, but at least it is a shared ground to build on top of. [? if psc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: They are, at least, currently supporting our government. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_psc: Governing together does bring some friction on top of that. ?][? if erc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_psc: We are already supporting a government they are a part of. Not being part of it is bringing some friction though. ?]By doing this, we may be somewhat alienating our more Catalanist allies to our right.


