Àngel Ros's PSC has taken a risky but commendable stance on Federal Catalanism. Breaking with the PSOE may not have been an easy move, but it has given them a lot more breathing room and a chance to stand for themselves. We have much to build together! [? if psc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: They are, on top of that, currently supporting our government. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_psc: Governing together does bring some friction, though. ?][? if erc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_psc: We are already supporting a government they are a part of. Not being part of it is bringing some friction though. ?]By doing this, we may be somewhat alienating our more Catalanist allies to our right.


