Montserrat Tura has taken the PSC through a bold and commendable reform. Not only she has broken with the PSOE, but has moved the party to the left and has now a radical confederalist, pro-self-determination position that we could have only wished for just a few years ago. We have much to build together! [? if psc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_erc: They are, on top of that, currently supporting our government. ?][? if erc_in_gob and cat_coalition_includes_psc: Governing together does bring some friction, though. ?][? if erc_supporting and cat_coalition_includes_psc: We are already supporting a government they are a part of. Not being part of it is bringing some friction though. ?]By doing this, we may be somewhat alienating our more Catalanist allies to our right.

@pdcat_split_relations
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: party_resources >= 1
view-if: pdcat_split
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources
on-arrival: {!
    Q.party_resources -= 1;
    Q.pdcat_relations += 5*(1 - Q.erc_dissent/100);
    if (Q.junts_formed) {
        Q.junts_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.jxcat_formed && !Q.erc_in_jxcat) {
        Q.jxcat_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.dl_formed) {
        Q.dl_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.cdc_formed) {
        Q.cdc_relations -= 2;
    } else if (Q.pdcat_formed) {
        Q.pdcat_relations -= 2;
    } else {
        Q.ciu_relations -= 2;
    }
    if (Q.csqp_formed) {
        Q.csqp_relations -= 3;
    } else if (Q.cecp_formed) {
        Q.cecp_relations -= 3;
    } else if (Q.ecp_formed) {
        Q.ecp_relations -= 3;
    } else {
        Q.icv_relations -= 3;
    }
    Q.cup_relations -= 3;
    Q.erc_parlament_barcelona_ind_support -= 1.5;
    Q.erc_parlament_girona_ind_support -= 1;
    Q.erc_parlament_lleida_ind_support -= 1;
    Q.erc_parlament_tarragona_ind_support -= 1.5;

    Q.erc_left_dissent += 5;
!}

The move to improve our relations with the now-separated, unapologetically bourgeois pdcat is a risky move. They sure are, on paper, pro-independence, but they are far from popular and not particularly well-liked by parties closer to us, both to our right and to our left. It may even alienate some of our more working-class voters. Only time will tell if this move was worth it.

